# TypeScript Import Conventions

## Type-Only Imports

Always use `import type` when importing types from any module:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
import type { ReactNode, CSSProperties, ElementType } from "react";

// ❌ Incorrect
import { ReactNode, CSSProperties, ElementType } from "react";
```

This applies to all type imports, not just React:

```tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react-vite";
import type { VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
```

## Mixed Imports

When importing both values and types from the same module, use separate import statements:

```tsx
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import type { ReactNode, FC } from "react";
```

## Benefits

- Enables better tree-shaking and smaller bundles
- Makes it explicit what is a type vs a runtime value
- Types are erased at compile time, clarifying intent
